extends layout

block content
    h1.display-2.custom-heading2(style="text-align: center;") About GeoBound
    p.p-4.fw-light.custom-box(style='font-size: 20px; text-align: center;')
      | GeoBound is a web app that helps users stay accountable to their commitments through location services. For example, if you set a commitment to go to the gym three times a week, GeoBound will only allow you to log that commitment as complete if you are physically at the gym. 
      br 
      br
      | Whether you are trying to go to the gym more often, study at the library, or simply get to your classes, you can be sure that you are always on the right track to achieving your goals.


    // About Us Info
    section#info
      .intro
        .caption
          h2.custom-heading3(style="text-align: center;")  Frequently Asked Questions
      .faq-content.bg-light
        .faq-question
          input#q1.panel(type='checkbox')
          .plus +
          label.panel-title(for='q1')
            | Is GeoBound a paid service?
          .panel-content
            | GeoBound is a completely free to use service with no add-ons.
        .faq-question
          input#q2.panel(type='checkbox')
          .plus +
          label.panel-title(for='q2') Does GeoBound offer a premium service?
          .panel-content
            | The full experience is completely free of charge through our web application.
        .faq-question
          input#q3.panel(type='checkbox')
          .plus +
          label.panel-title(for='q3') Who developed GeoBound?
          .panel-content
            | JP, Ram, Rogelio, and Steven. sup
        .faq-question
          input#q4.panel(type='checkbox')
          .plus +
          label.panel-title(for='q4') What platforms can I access GeoBound on?
          .panel-content
            | You can use GeoBound on any platform that can access the internet.

      .p-4.w-50.mx-auto.custom-box
        p.fw-light.m-0(style='font-size: 20px;')
          b Built with: 
          | node.js, Pug, MongoDB, Bootstrap, express.js, Redis, enough caffeine to kill two people

    style.
      @import url(https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway);
      body {
        overflow-x: hidden;
      }
      .faq-header{
        font-size: 42px;
        border-bottom: 2px dotted #ccc;
        padding: 24px;
      }
      .faq-content {
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
      .faq-question {
        padding: 20px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px dotted #ccc;
      }
      .panel-title {
        font-size: 24px;
        width: 100%;
        position: relative;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 10px 10px 0 48px;
        display: block;
        cursor: pointer;
      }
      .panel-content {
        font-size: 15px;
        padding: 0px 14px;
        margin: 0 40px;
        height: 0;
        overflow: hidden;
        position: relative;
        -webkit-transition: .4s ease;
        -moz-transition: .4s ease;
        -o-transition: .4s ease;
        transition: .4s ease;
      }
      .panel:checked ~ .panel-content{
        height: auto;
        opacity: 1;
        padding: 14px;
      }
      .plus {
        position: absolute;
        margin-left: 15px;
        margin-top: 0px;
        z-index: 5;
        font-size: 42px;
        line-height: 100%;
        -webkit-user-select: none;
        -moz-user-select: none;
        -ms-user-select: none;
        -o-user-select: none;
        user-select: none;
        -webkit-transition: .2s ease;
        -moz-transition: .2s ease;
        -o-transition: .2s ease;
        transition: .2s ease;
      }
      .panel:checked ~ .plus {
        -webkit-transform: rotate(45deg);
        -moz-transform: rotate(45deg);
        -o-transform: rotate(45deg);
        transform: rotate(45deg);
        color: #3EB489;
      }
      .panel {
        display: none;
      }
